# FreeCRM Deployment

## Local dev (`dev.itconnect.pl`)

**Same environment as the WSL repo + `docker compose` — not a separate host.** Nginx in `docker/nginx/default.conf` serves the bind-mounted tree; `FREECRM_SITE_URL` is `https://dev.itconnect.pl/`. MCP browser and manual browser QA on that URL hit local PHP/DB. No `pushsrc` needed for local changes.

## Remote test server (`test.itconnect.pl`)

- Host: `test.itconnect.pl`, root `/opt/freecrm`, manage via `docker compose`.
- SSH: `bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl`.
- HTTPS: Let's Encrypt via Cloudflare DNS (`certbot/dns-cloudflare`, creds in `docker/nginx/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini`). Nginx reads `docker/nginx/certs/{host}.{fullchain,privkey}.pem` only — after issue/renew, copy from `letsencrypt/live/` (see `renewal/*.conf`). Privkeys: `640`, group `www-data` (nginx uid 33).
- Hostnames: `test.itconnect.pl` on remote server; `dev.itconnect.pl` → local Docker only (see above).
- Services: `web`, `app`, `cron`, `db`.
- Cron: `docker compose up -d cron` runs `cron/vtigercron.php` every minute via supercronic; log at `cache/logs/cron.log`. CV **file** sync (prod backup → `import/cv/pending`) is a separate supercronic job; CRM import is **two** cron tasks (applications + candidates) — see `docker-commands.mdc` → CV application file sync. Restart `cron` after cv-sync script/config changes.
- Storage: `/opt/freecrm/storage` (copied from `10.0.0.220:/var/www/yetiforce/storage`).
- Migration backups: `/opt/freecrm/_migration`; local rollback dump at `tmp/migration-20260511-134258/`.

## TLS (issue / renew)

From repo root; replace `HOST` (`dev.itconnect.pl` or `test.itconnect.pl`):

```bash
docker run --rm \
  -v "$PWD/docker/nginx/letsencrypt:/etc/letsencrypt" \
  -v "$PWD/docker/nginx/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini:/etc/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini:ro" \
  certbot/dns-cloudflare certonly --dns-cloudflare \
  --dns-cloudflare-credentials /etc/letsencrypt/cloudflare.ini \
  --dns-cloudflare-propagation-seconds 60 \
  -d HOST --key-type ecdsa --non-interactive --agree-tos --register-unsafely-without-email

sudo cp docker/nginx/letsencrypt/live/HOST/fullchain.pem docker/nginx/certs/HOST.fullchain.pem
sudo cp docker/nginx/letsencrypt/live/HOST/privkey.pem docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem
sudo chgrp www-data docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem && sudo chmod 640 docker/nginx/certs/HOST.privkey.pem
```

Renew: same mounts, `certbot/dns-cloudflare renew --cert-name HOST`, then recopy + reload nginx (`docker compose exec web nginx -s reload` on server).

## Sync to test (`scripts/sync-freecrm.sh`)

**Do not read the script before syncing** — use this section. Run all commands from repo root.

**Target (defaults):** `bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl:/opt/freecrm`. Override: `FREECRM_SYNC_REMOTE_HOST`, `FREECRM_SYNC_REMOTE_USER`, `FREECRM_SYNC_REMOTE_PATH`.

| Subcommand | Use when |
|---|---|
| `pushsrc` | Code, layouts, migrations, `user_privileges/` templates — **default deploy** |
| `pushdb` | Overwrite **test** DB with local dump (destructive on test) |
| `pushstorage` | Push `storage/` blobs to test (additive; no `--delete`) |
| `pushall` | `pushsrc` + `pushdb` + `pushstorage` (full local → test) |
| `pulldb` | Pull test DB → local (destructive on local) |

`pushsrc` rsyncs with `--delete`, excludes `.git/`, `.cursor/`, `cache/`, `storage/`, `tmp/`, `_migration/`, clears remote `cache/templates_c/*/*.php`. Does **not** restart containers.

DB subcommands (`pushdb`, `pushall`, `pulldb`) prompt for confirmation unless `FREECRM_SYNC_YES=1` (agents: always set for non-interactive).

### Standard deploy — code + migrations (most tasks)

After explicit user approval:

```bash
./scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushsrc
ssh bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl 'cd /opt/freecrm && docker compose exec -T app php yii migrate --migrationPath=migrations/Users/ --interactive=0 && docker compose exec -T app php bin/regenerate_user_privileges.php'
```

- Run migrate when the change added/applied `migrations/Users/*.php`.
- `regenerate_user_privileges.php` rebuilds `tabdata.php`, `user_privileges_*.php`, `menu_*.php` on the **server** from server DB — required after profile/menu migrations.
- LinkAction DB: `migrationPath=migrations/LinkAction/` instead of/in addition to Users.
- Menu-only cache: if migrate touched `yetiforce_menu` and menus look stale, run regenerate anyway (`refreshMenuFiles()` inside migrate is unreliable).

### Other recipes

```bash
# Code only (no new migrations)
./scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushsrc

# Storage blobs only
./scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushstorage

# Full test refresh from local (destructive test DB)
FREECRM_SYNC_YES=1 ./scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushall

# Pull test DB to local dev
FREECRM_SYNC_YES=1 ./scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pulldb

# Single migration file without full pushsrc (rare)
rsync -az migrations/Users/mXXXX_....php bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl:/opt/freecrm/migrations/Users/
ssh bmankowski@test.itconnect.pl 'cd /opt/freecrm && docker compose exec -T app php yii migrate --migrationPath=migrations/Users/ --interactive=0'
```

Remote PHP/compose always via SSH + `docker compose exec -T app …` (no host `php` on the server).

**Agent policy:** never run `pushsrc`, `pushdb`, `pushall`, or `pulldb` without explicit user approval. Once approved, run the matching recipe above directly — no need to open `sync-freecrm.sh`.
